We believe that ‚ÄúSnacking is a part of life and our passion makes it better‚Äù.
who we are
We produce iconic brands that satisfy snackers across the globe. With one of the largest distribution networks in the business and an advanced research & development team, we‚Äôre well positioned for the future.

what we make
We pride ourselves on making quality snacks for any occasion. Whether you‚Äôre looking to try something new or your old favorites, our snacks are perfect for your pantry, your lunchbox and everything in between.

why we matter
At Snyder‚Äôs-Lance we appreciate the importance of corporate social responsibility (CSR). Not only are we guided by our company‚Äôs history and values, it is our mission to support the community, protect the environment, and make our great products even better.
how we will succeedInnovative New ProductsWe are uniquely positioned to continuously deliver new products across our entire product portfolioOutstanding PartnershipOur employees are dedicated to providing the best experience possible for our partnersExtraordinary Place to WorkOur employees enjoy competitive benefits and a great work life balanceExcellent Shareholder ReturnsWe believe in continuous improvement and capturing efficiencies in order to deliver sustainable shareholder value creationthe history of Snyder‚Äôs-Lance      1909 Harry V. Warehime first began making pretzels for the Hanover Pretzel Company, which later became Snyder‚Äôs of Hanover
         1913 Philip L. Lance, began selling roasted peanuts on the streets of Charlotte and soon after the Lance peanut butter sandwich cracker was born
         1982 Lance, Inc. introduced the Home-Pak, a special packaged product designed to grow supermarket sales
         1992 Snyder‚Äôs of Hanover introduced the Honey Mustard and Onion Pretzel Pieces
         1999 Lance, Inc. purchased Cape Cod¬Æ, maker of high quality kettle chips with a distinctive crunch and unique flavor
         2010 Snyder‚Äôs of Hanover and Lance, Inc. announced the merger of equals creating Snyder‚Äôs-Lance, Inc.
         2012 Snyder‚Äôs-Lance acquiredSnack Factory¬Æ Pretzel Crisps¬Æ, the world's first pretzel-shaped cracker
         2014 Snyder‚Äôs-Lance purchased Baptista's Bakery, Inc. an industry leader in developing innovative snacks. That same year, the company increased investment in Late July¬Æ Organic Snacks, creating another core brand for the company
         2015 Introduced a new company logo and purpose statement. Also announced a new division called Clearview Foods focused on developing innovative and ‚Äúbetter for you‚Äù snacking options
         2016 Snyder‚Äôs-Lance acquired Diamond Foods¬Æ, including KETTLE Brand¬Æ and KETTLE¬Æ Chips, Pop Secret¬Æ and Emerald¬Æ. The acquisition strengthened the company‚Äôs commitment to ‚Äúbetter for you‚Äù snacks and expanded its national footprint.         
