roducts through direct-store-delivery network, third-party distributors, and directly to grocery/mass merchandisers, club stores, discount stores, convenience stores, and food service establishments, as well as various other retail customers, such as drug stores, schools, military and government facilities, recreational facilities, offices, and other independent retailers. The company was formerly known as Lance, Inc. and changed its name to Snyder¬ís-Lance, Inc. in December 2010. Snyder¬ís-Lance, Inc. was founded in 1912 and is headquartered in Charlotte, North Carolina.Corporate GovernanceSnyder's-Lance, Inc.‚Äôs ISS Governance QualityScore as of July 1, 2017 is 7. The pillar scores are Audit: 1; Board: 7; Shareholder Rights: 10; Compensation: 3.Corporate governance scores courtesy of Institutional Shareholder Services (ISS).  Scores indicate decile rank relative to index or region. A decile score of 1 indicates lower governance risk, while a 10 indicates higher governance risk.Yahoo Small BusinessData DisclaimerHelpSuggestionsPrivacyAbout Our AdsTerms (Updated)








